flowRoot.flowPara: Many Social Systems have a Gypsy Cemetery. Initially there would be one dead kid, gypsy... Maybe the one that was just ignored or forgot by the group. Some older people used things like the m37 card then finally using then the dt1 crad. Even if the group did say no to m37 they still would feel bad about the death of an equal aged, also if someone from the older generation pushed the red button.

An additional problem would be to have the next "choosen one" as scapegoat "to protect the group" so he would ask a lot of questions and then would problably find out about that dirthy game. So you would have a transitive situation where all the older people would have to attack the youngest asking [the right|to many] questions.
